# Quick Reference for Common Tasks

When the user asks how to:

## "Run my website locally"
Just open index.html in a browser! No server needed for this simple site.
Or use Live Server extension in VS Code for auto-refresh.

## "Add a new project"
1. Add images to /images folder
2. Create new HTML file in /projects folder (copy from project1.html)
3. Add link to the new project on index.html

## "Change colors/fonts"
Edit style.css file - look for CSS variables at the top (--primary-color, etc.)

## "Put my website online"
This is a GitHub Pages site! Just push changes to the repository.
URL: https://studiodaria.github.io

## "My images are loading slowly"
Use squoosh.app to compress images before uploading.
Recommended: max 1920px width, quality 80%.
